revisions.description: Change OCTET STRING to DisplayString for all MIBs.
Change the MAX-ACCESS for the logIndex to not-accessible.
Updated enumeration type to use INTEGER.
MIB revision history dates in descriptions updated.

log.description: The AT Log MIB, for listing log entries from the buffered and permament logs.

logTable.name: logTable
logTable.description: A list of log entries from the source specified in the logSource object. The list is ordered from oldest entry to newest entry.

logEntry.name: logEntry
logEntry.description: A log entry from the source specified in the logSource object.

logIndex.name: logIndex
logIndex.description: An index value. This index is not directly tied to any specific log entry. Over time, the log will grow larger and eventually older entries will be removed.

logDate.name: logDate
logDate.description: The date that the log was generated, in the form YYYY MMM DD, eg: 2008 Oct 9.

logTime.name: logTime
logTime.description: The time that the log was generated, in the form HH:MM:SS, eg: 07:15:04.

logFacility.name: logFacility
logFacility.description: The syslog facility that generated the log entry. See the Software Reference Manual for more information.

logSeverity.name: logSeverity
logSeverity.description: The severity level of the log entry: emerg Emergency, system is unusable alert Action must be taken immediately crit Critical conditions err Error conditions warning Warning conditions notice Normal, but significant, conditions info Informational messages debug Debug-level messages

logProgram.name: logProgram
logProgram.description: The program that generated the log entry. See the Software Reference Manual for more information.

logSource.name: logSource
logSource.description: The source to retrieve the log entries from. Valid values are: 1 - Buffered log 2 - Permanent log This source is used when retrieving the logTable objects, and also specifies the log to be cleared when the clearLog object is set.

logAll.name: logAll
logAll.description: Determines the quantity of logs to be retrieved. Valid values are: 0 - Display only recent log messages 1 - Show all available log entries. Note: Choosing to retrieve all log entries may result in a delay of several seconds before they may be viewed via SNMP.

clearLog.name: clearLog
clearLog.description: Set with a value of 1 to clear the log that is specified by the logSource object.
